<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1932-10-29T06:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1932-10-29T06:00:00-05:00" n="262" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d262">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">662.116 Fruit/35: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Germany (<persName corresp="#p_GGA1" type="from">Gordon</persName>) to the
                                        <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Berlin</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-10-29T12:00:00+01:00">October 29,
                                        1932—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received October 29—9:10
                                    a.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>211. Department’s 126, October 28, noon. I have again taken occasion
                                to impress upon the German Government our position in this matter as
                                outlined in Department’s 124, October 21, 6 p.m.</p>
                            <closer><signed><persName corresp="#p_GGA1"><hi rend="smallcaps">Gordon</hi></persName></signed></closer>
                            <postscript>
                                <p>[The files of the Department appear to contain no continuation of
                                    correspondence on this subject.]</p>
                            </postscript>
                        </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>